## Context
The ticket spec defines validation rules (required headers, no
duplicate IDs, valid Status values) but no validator exists.
Pre-commit hook has no ticket checks. `make check` has no ticket
checks.

## Relevant files
- `hooks/pre-commit` — add ticket validation call
- `Makefile` — add `validate-tickets` to `check` and `check-fast`
- `scripts/validate_tickets.py` — new script

## Actions
1. Write `scripts/validate_tickets.py`:
   - Parse all `tickets/*.ticket` files (RFC 822 headers + separators)
   - Check required headers: Id, Title, Author, Status, Created
   - Check Id matches filename pattern (`{id}-*.ticket`)
   - Reject duplicate Ids across all ticket files
   - Validate Status values (open, doing, closed)
   - Validate Blocked-by references point to existing ticket Ids
   - Validate X-Phase values if present
   - Exit 0 on success, exit 1 with diagnostics on failure
2. Add `validate-tickets` target to Makefile
3. Wire into `check-fast` and `check` targets
4. Add ticket validation to pre-commit hook (guard 6)

## Test
First test: `test_validate_tickets.py`
- Valid ticket file passes
- Missing required header fails
- Duplicate Id fails with suggested suffix
- Blocked-by pointing to nonexistent Id fails
- Id/filename mismatch fails

## Verification
- [ ] `make check-fast` runs ticket validation
- [ ] Pre-commit rejects a ticket with duplicate Id
- [ ] Existing tickets all pass validation

## Exit criteria
- All existing tickets pass validation
- `make check-fast` includes ticket validation
- Pre-commit hook includes ticket validation
